<concept id="a075c8d4def2da92d92e5bd0139afc6c" xml:lang="en-US">
   <title>Interactive Queries</title>
   <prolog>
      <source>ST4 ID: 14578481803</source>
      <permissions view="ericsson_internal"/>
      <metadata>
         <othermeta content="NA" name="workitem"/>
      </metadata>
      <resourceid id="NA"/>
   </prolog>
   <conbody>
      <p>The Impala shell tool can be used to open interactive sessions with Impala servers for ad hoc queries and exploration.</p>
      <note id="note_N1002F_N10028_N10001">
         <p>Execute the following commands on the Impala <ph keyref=""/>.</p>
      </note>
      <ul id="ul_af5_r2y_1lb">
         <li>
            <p>To connect to an Impala server with the Impala shell:</p>
            <p><userinput>docker exec -it impala-server impala-shell -i localhost</userinput></p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To execute an ad hoc query on an Impala server with the Impala shell:</p>
            <p><userinput>docker exec -it impala-server impala-shell -i localhost -q
                  "${query}"</userinput></p>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>The Impala shell accepts SQL statements listed in the <xref format="html" href="https://www.cloudera.com/documentation/enterprise/5-9-x/topics/impala_langref_sql.html#langref_sql" scope="external">Impala SQL Statements</xref> in Cloudera.</p>
   </conbody>
</concept>